# Project Standards

## Code Formatting

- Use 2 spaces for indentation (no tabs)
- No semicolons at end of statements
- No trailing commas
- Use Prettier for formatting (configured in `.prettierrc`)

## Import Organization

Organize imports in this exact order with comments:

```typescript
// System
import { useState } from "react"
import clsx from "clsx"
// Lib
import { trpc } from "@/lib/trpc/client"
import { useSetCharacterId } from "@/lib/trpc/hooks"
// Store
import { useStore } from "@/store"
// Components
import SomeComponent from "@/components/SomeComponent"
// Ui
import Button from "@/ui/Actions/Button"
import Beam from "@/ui/Layout/Beam"
// Constants
import { MODAL_LIST } from "@/constants/modalList"
// Styles and types
import { ComponentProps } from "./types"
import styles from "./styles.module.scss"
```

**Note**: Include "Lib" section when using tRPC or other library utilities. Include "Components" section when importing other components.

## Path Aliases

- Use `@/*` alias for imports from `src/*`
- Example: `import Button from "@/ui/Actions/Button"`

## File Naming

- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `Header.tsx`, `ModalContainer.tsx`)
- API routes: `route.ts` (Next.js App Router convention)
- Types: `types.ts` (co-located with component)
- Database models: PascalCase (e.g., `Character.ts`, `Player.ts`)

## Component Structure

- Components should have `index.tsx` and `types.ts` files
- Use default exports for components
- Place types in separate `types.ts` file, not inline

## TypeScript

- Use strict mode (enabled in `tsconfig.json`)
- Prefer interfaces over types for object shapes
- Use generic types where appropriate (e.g., `FormProps<FormValues>`)
- Always type function parameters and return types
